War II, was flying his F-8 Crusader on a routine

00:01:43.759 --> 00:01:46.060
flight at 47,000 feet.

00:01:46.060 --> 00:01:51.969
At 6PM, because of the engine failure, his
was forced to eject into -50 �C (-58 �F)

00:01:51.969 --> 00:01:52.969
air.

00:01:52.969 --> 00:01:56.969
Without a pressure suit, this was a life threatening
choice.

00:01:56.969 --> 00:01:59.270
But this wasn't his biggest problem.

00:01:59.270 --> 00:02:04.210
Since at the time he was flying over a heavy
thunderstorm cloud, when he ejected, he found

00:02:04.210 --> 00:02:06.700
himself in the midst of a beast.

00:02:06.700 --> 00:02:11.660
Lightning appeared, which he described as
blue blades several feet thick, and thunder

00:02:11.660 --> 00:02:13.160
